# Phase 10: Gemini AI Engine & "Bring Your Own Browser" Scraping

To take the tracking engine to the next level, we will replace the backend LLM with the **Gemini AI Engine**. We will also deeply enhance the scraping engine to support **Persistent Chrome Sessions**, allowing the automation to explicitly borrow your personal, logged-in Google and Facebook sessions directly!

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> Please review the two architectural upgrades below before I execute the code.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Part 1: Gemini AI Migration
We will strip out the OpenAI SDK and migrate the intelligence backend entirely to the Gemini API.

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/settings/page.tsx` & `targetList.json`
- We will replace `openaiApiKey` with `geminiApiKey`. 
- The UI will be updated to accept the Gemini API Key.

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/api/synthesize/route.ts`
- Install the official `@google/generative-ai` SDK.
- Rewrite the prompt execution to utilize **`gemini-1.5-flash`** (or `gemini-1.5-pro`).
- Leverage Gemini's natively enforced `response_mime_type: "application/json"` to guarantee the exact output schema needed for the Polymorphic Views.

---

### Part 2: "Bring Your Own Browser" (BYOB) Scraping
Right now, the scraper tries to spin up a completely fresh, empty "incognito" style headless browser heavily locked down by bot protection—OR it expects a WebSocket endpoint for a specialized app like AdsPower. 

To scrape Facebook or logged-in exclusive areas, we will implement **Persistent Contexts**.

#### [MODIFY] `src/lib/scraper/engine.ts`
- We will introduce a new launch mode: **Persistent Chrome Profile**.
- Instead of using a random headless browser, we will use `chromium.launchPersistentContext()` and point it directly to a local Chrome User Data Directory.
- **Why this works**: When Playwright boots up, it will literally look like your regular Chrome browser, already securely logged into Facebook, Reddit, and X via your real cookies. 
- It will simply open a new tab automatically, parse the specific page you want rapidly, and close the tab without you needing to do anything manually!

